parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To will, wish, desire, be willing, intend, design.
From the same as oikodome; to be a house-builder, i.e. Construct or confirm.
A tower, fortified structure. Apparently a primary word; a tower or castle.
By no means, not at all. Intensive of ou; not indeed.
First, in the first place, before, formerly. Neuter of protos as adverb; firstly.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Another form for kathezomai; to seat down, i.e. Set; intransitively, to sit; figuratively, to settle.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To reckon, compute, calculate. From psephos; to use pebbles in enumeration, i.e. to compute.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To have, hold, possess. Including an alternate form scheo skheh'-o; a primary verb; to hold.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Completion, perfection. From a derivative of aparti; completion.
